column20: Much chasing about at hen cluster
column27: 1m - but she moved away after 1 minute
column33: 7:50 falcon flew over lek. Master cock didn't stay strutting but everyone else did. Falcon nearly killed him - he lived but immediately began strutting again after the prairie falcon passed by!

West mating center crowded when first arrived but always dispercing forwards W/W hens (?) stream. W/W had another fight at 6:55 w/ unidentified male - standoff. Again at 7:00. Female with orange on left, clustered near W/W, appears to be O/W?

column20: W/W now has 22 females surrounding him

column33: 2 mating centeres at beginning, most males and females were at one on hill. By 6:45, hens had moved to center by creek. Several males were walking back and forth between centers.

Y/R last chase to UM male. Y/P male chaesd off by UM male. 7:12 - immature golden eagle flew over - (?) all (?) but W/O who is still (?). Marked males: WY, YW, YR, YO, OW, WO, OG, YB, WR, YG, YP. Markes hens: WW, YP.

column28: chased juv male, wing fight with O/G - won
just sat - chased UM male off

column14: W/ consider while open space between patches
column20: still too dark to see females
column33: WO lost fight to unmarked bird. WO - bloodied. Lek breaking up male follow last 2 females - lots of juvenile males (?), lots of fights and chases. 7:10 - lek spread out very far females everywhere. Females - YR, RR, YP.

column20: Very spread out both males and females

column33: Eagle on dam when leaving. Males: W-Y male, R-R female, W-R male, Y-W male, Y-G male.

column13: Disturbance by G+F photo crew. Wind picking up at 6:23.
column33: 6:5 copulation interrupted. 7:00 Y/P chased another male out of central cluster. Y/W missing nearly 1/2 of tail feathers. Marked females: /B, G/G, Marked males: W/Y, Y/R, W/R, W/W, Y/P, Y/W.
Master cock not marked. Two interrupted copulation of the MC by his nearby (?).

column28: chased off by  master cock and YB

column33: Not much strutting - interrupted by a coyote early then by a marsh hawk. Tag YG, YO.
2 males fighting next to two females - bumped one male then she flew off lek. At 6:06 the female had walked off to N and strutting dropped markedly

column28: Confronted by juvenile male - appeared to stimulate strutting

column33: Y/G is ~ 300 yards from other males. 6:51 - Y/B won another fight. W/Y on hill to the W of the main lek. There are 5 females over there including W/Y. W/O mostly by himself, closest female 15-20m.

column28: Clucking + tail wagging w/ UM male, standoff
column33: Left at 6:15 to see if birds on E half of lek - now there. Hen did not seem interested in males - was actually chased off by UM male. Left lek at 5:35 - no copulation. 6:00 - Y/P in tail wagging contest with some UM male W/O had standoff with. Strutting increased for all birds at sunrise, but stopped soon after.

column28: Clucking + tail wagging w/ UM male, standoff
Cluck and tail wagging UM male

column33: 6:10 - 2 hens in drain W of lek - one walked by O/Y who was on ridge WY (?), but not on the lek at all. 5:35 - hen flew north. 5:33 - everyone crouched down for 1 min. Why? W/O - tail wagging, clucking w/ UM male. Y/B - chased off by UM male. 5:57 - hen back on ridge of lek - males increased strutting, walked by lek and left. Hen seemed to pursue O/Y.

column28: walked at UM male, fed whole time

column13: Cattle placed on range 12 May 1988 (stupid ones)
column28: hens moved off W side of lek. Chased and eyeing W/ juv - won
column33: SPACEMAN SPIFF SURROUNDED BY COWS!! O/Y from 12 May 1988 is O/W from last year - feathers not ripped. UM juv watching fight got chased off + happened (?)! W/O and others - following hens as they moved. Y/B in big fight w/ UM male - eveying (?), etc., standoff. 6:05 - large raptor flew in (not eagle), birds crouched, but did not fly. Did not scare cows. COWS ARE EVERYWHERE!! MOOING, DROOLING, POOPING!! One hen hung out w/ O/W most of morning, then dissapeared into drain behind lek. O/W followed, but to no avail. 2nd hen in group of males on lek w/ Y/B. She finally solicited at 7:30 - interupted copulation. Kept soliciting - got by UM male at 7:38.
